│ **1. Analysis of the Crash:**                                                                                                                                                            │
│ The crash occurs in `instcombine` when processing a `shufflevector` instruction whose operand is a `select` instruction. The `shufflevector` changes the vector length from `<2 x        │
│ float>` to `<4 x float>`. The stack trace shows the crash happens inside `FoldOpIntoSelect`, which is called from `visitShuffleVectorInst`. This function tries to transform             │
